Agricultural and Biological Chemistry Bu.directions: Near the CAFS cluster, behind the Soils Building. Look for the ABC signage.

AFBED Building.directions: Part of the CEAT complex. Located near the Agricultural and Bio-Resource Engineering area.

Animal Science Building.directions: In the CAFS area, past the crop science buildings. Look for the animal husbandry facilities nearby.

Biological Sciences Building.directions: In front of CAS Annex 1, to the left of SEARCA. Has multiple wings (BS A, B, C, D, E) housing the Institute of Biological Sciences.

CAFS Building.directions: College of Agriculture and Food Science cluster. In the upper campus area near the agriculture facilities.
CAFS Building.aka: College of Agriculture and Food Science

CAS Main Building.directions: The main CAS building is BEHIND the Oblation statue. CAS Bxx rooms are in the basement (stairs in front of OCS kiosks). CAS 1xx rooms are on the first floor. CAS LITE rooms are on the 2nd floor.

CAS Annex 1.directions: The tall 4-floor building to the LEFT of Oble, beside OUR (Office of the University Registrar). Has galleries (GAL) on lower floors and lecture rooms on floors 3-4.

CAS Annex 2.directions: The 2-storey building beside CAS Annex 1, to the left of Oble.

CDC Building.directions: College of Development Communication building. Located at Carabao Park, in front of the Administration Building.

Civil Engineering Building.directions: Part of the CEAT cluster. Near the main engineering buildings.

CEAT Building.directions: College of Engineering and Agro-Industrial Technology complex. The CEAT shops and labs are here.
CEAT Building.aka: College of Engineering and Agro-Industrial Technology

CEM Building.directions: College of Economics and Management. The first cluster of buildings if you follow the Kanan road from the main gate. A large building complex with many lecture rooms (CEM 101-118, 201-205).

CFNR Building.directions: College of Forestry and Natural Resources. Located in the upper campus. Has multiple buildings and facilities.
CFNR Building.aka: College of Forestry and Natural Resources

rooms: Dean's Office Conference Room DECL Hall
Dean's Office Conference Room, DECL Hall
CHE Building.directions: College of Human Ecology (Gil F. Saguiguit Hall). Located beside Physical Sciences, on the left side of OPark when facing the Oblation.

Chemical Engineering Building.directions: In the CEAT complex, has specialized labs including Unit Operations. Near the other engineering buildings.

rooms: DVCS ZOTC Rm - Gregorio San Agustin Hall
CVM Building.directions: College of Veterinary Medicine. Located behind the Carillon Tower. Has multiple facilities including Fronda Hall.

DAAE Building.directions: Department of Agricultural and Applied Economics. Part of the CEM cluster.

Electrical Engineering Building.aka: Dante De Padua Hall (CEAT Administrative Building)
Electrical Engineering Building.directions: White, three-storey building beside ICrops in Pili Drive. Part of CEAT complex. Houses EE lecture rooms and the EE Auditorium.

Forestry Biological Sciences Building.directions: In the CFNR area in the upper campus. Contains FBS labs and lecture rooms.

Graduate School Building.directions: Behind the International House dormitory, at the foot of the ascent going to UHS and Forestry.

Hydrology Building.directions: The Hydrology Laboratory. Located in the CEAT area, near the irrigation and water resources facilities.

IABE Building.directions: Institute of Agricultural and Biosystems Engineering. In the CEAT area.

ICOPED Building.directions: Institute of Cooperatives and Bio-Enterprise Development. Part of the CEM area.

ICropS Building.directions: Institute of Crop Science building. In the CAFS cluster. The iLab here is for Institute of Crop Science, NOT ICS (Computer Science)!

Industrial Engineering Building.directions: Part of CEAT. Contains IE lecture rooms and labs.

IFST Building.directions: Institute of Food Science and Technology. In the CAFS cluster, has main building and several annexes (A, B, C, D) including pilot plant facilities.

IHNF Building.directions: Institute of Human Nutrition and Food. Part of the CHE building complex.

IRNR Building.directions: Institute of Renewable Natural Resources. Part of the CFNR complex in the upper campus.

IWEP Building.directions: Institute of Weed Science, Entomology and Plant Pathology. In the CAFS area, includes the WPD Hall.

LHKCB Building.directions: Near the CAFS area. Has lecture halls and classroom facilities.

Math Building.directions: The old-looking building on the left before the bridge to CEAT, just across the Diocesan Shrine of St. Therese. Houses IMSP lecture rooms (MB 100-104 on ground floor, MB 301-309 on 3rd floor).

Copeland Gymnasium.directions: The main gym facility. From the main gate, it's on the right side before reaching the academic buildings. Has 3 floors - Wing B is towards the parking at the back. Contains various sports facilities including courts and training areas.

Baker Hall Pool.directions: The swimming pool area, located behind Baker Hall, which is at Freedom Park. Managed by the Department of Human Kinetics (CAS).

PHTRC Building.directions: Post-Harvest Training and Research Center. In the CAFS area.

Physical Sciences Building.directions: Francisco O. Santos Hall. A wide building to the RIGHT of Oble. Has PSLH (Physical Science Lecture Halls) A and B, plus many PS rooms (B-100 to B-205, C-101 to C-320).

PTCF Building.directions: Post-harvest Training and Research Center Facility. In the CAFS area.

TCC Building.directions: Temporary Common Classroom at the Old Maquiling School. Located beside the CHE building, behind the Administration Building. Has multiple rooms (TCC 1, 2, 4, 5, 11, 22).

Main Library.directions: The main library building. Located behind the Pegaraw statue (winged tamaraw).

UPRHS Building.directions: UP Rural High School. Located in Bay, Laguna, OUTSIDE the main UPLB campus.
